  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/76890864" />
    <a title="JenMcJ" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2114981-jenmcj"><img alt="JenMcJ" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1278367694p2/2114981.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/76890864?book_show_action=true">Nov 06, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="JenMcJ" class="user" itemprop="url" name="JenMcJ" href="/user/show/2114981-jenmcj">JenMcJ</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2114981-jenmcj?shelf=e-books">e-books</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2114981-jenmcj?shelf=mm-mmm-a-few-mmf-too">mm-mmm-a-few-mmf-too</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer76890864" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1286281974133132035">3.5 stars <br/><br/>This was a very well told story that could easily have sank into overwhelming bitterness and angst. Considering the storyline is weighty and filled with sadness and at times despair it is riveting.<br/><br/>Revolving around the recovery, heart and soul, of one man after senseless brutal violence takes his partner the story watches Eli climb out of mourning and back into living life again. <br/><br/>This book is touching and emotional as we watch Alec reach Eli and help him move forward. Interestingly this</span>
  <span id="freeText1286281974133132035" style="display:none">3.5 stars <br /><br />This was a very well told story that could easily have sank into overwhelming bitterness and angst. Considering the storyline is weighty and filled with sadness and at times despair it is riveting.<br /><br />Revolving around the recovery, heart and soul, of one man after senseless brutal violence takes his partner the story watches Eli climb out of mourning and back into living life again. <br /><br />This book is touching and emotional as we watch Alec reach Eli and help him move forward. Interestingly this book actually has no sex scenes. Not a single one. Since the book ends just as Alec and Eli really firmly reach out to each other we never see them as a full blown couple which is disappointing. After that much emotional investment into the two I felt like the story was just about to really get good and the payoff for all the tears I had shed was just at hand when it ended. <br /><br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="1286281974133132035" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
